sql:
SELECT epidemic_name, description
FROM epidemics
WHERE start_date > '2020-01-01';

SELECT user_id, COUNT(*) AS access_count
FROM data_access_logs
GROUP BY user_id;

external_knowledge:
- "Epicenters" metaphorically refers to the countries most affected by an epidemic; 
- "Bearing the brunt" implies suffering the most impact, here referring to having the highest number of confirmed cases;
- "Top three countries" refers to the countries with the highest number of confirmed cases per epidemic, as determined by the ranking in the SQL query.

sql:
SELECT username, role
FROM users
WHERE user_id = (SELECT user_id FROM data_access_logs WHERE log_id = 1);

SELECT COUNT(epidemic_id) 
FROM epidemics 
WHERE transmissibility > 1.0;
